          • Eighth-grade students analyze grade 3-5 learning progressions and design developmentally appropriate activities
        </p>
        <p>
          • Students create lesson plans, materials, and assessment strategies for younger learners
        </p>
        <p>
          • Weekly teaching sessions where eighth graders facilitate data science activities with elementary students
        </p>
        <p>
          • Reflection and iteration based on teaching experiences and student feedback
        </p>
        <p>
          <alert>Component 2: Community Action Research Projects</alert>
        </p>
